    {
      "page_number": 4,
      "width": 595.4400024414062,
      "height": 841.6799926757812,
      "blocks": [
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b1",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.0,
            96.86395263671875,
            378.0398864746094,
            113.59195709228516
          ],
          "text": "3.\nOperational Guidelines to avail the incentives -",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "Arial-BoldMT",
            "flags": 16,
            "is_bold": true,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b2",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.0,
            122.72393798828125,
            292.05853271484375,
            139.45193481445312
          ],
          "text": "3.1 Performance based incentives -",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "Arial-BoldMT",
            "flags": 16,
            "is_bold": true,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b3",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.0,
            148.6679229736328,
            552.3399047851562,
            212.27999877929688
          ],
          "text": "i) The incentives will be paid on the soiled notes actually received in the Issue Office of the RBI. Banks need not submit a separate claim in this regard. Currency chest branch will have to pass on the incentive to the linked branches for the soiled notes tendered by them on a pro-rata basis.",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "ArialMT",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
